<body>
<div class="top-bar">
  <h1>Documentation</h1>
  <a href="index.html" class="back-btn" id="backBtn">&larr; Back to app</a>
</div>
<script>try{if(window.self!==window.top)document.getElementById('backBtn').style.display='none';}catch(e){}</script>

<div class="container">

<h2>Getting started</h2>

<p>RD Style Sample Log replaces the handwritten customs declaration forms your buyers fill out when traveling to purchase samples. It runs on any phone, tablet, or laptop — no app install needed.</p>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">1</span><span class="step-title">Open the app</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Go to your app link in any browser. On iPhone, tap the Share button then "Add to Home Screen" to make it feel like a native app.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">2</span><span class="step-title">One-time setup</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Tap the <span class="kbd">&#9881;</span> gear icon in the top-right corner. Enter your send-to email address and your Anthropic API key (needed for photo scanning). Both are saved on your device — you only do this once.</div>
</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>Adding samples</h2>
<p>Tap <span class="kbd">+ Add sample</span> and choose one of two methods:</p>

<h3>Option A — Scan photos (recommended)</h3>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">1</span><span class="step-title">Take 3 photos</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Tap each photo slot to snap a picture of the <strong>price tag</strong>, <strong>content/care label</strong>, and the <strong>garment itself</strong>. You can use 1, 2, or all 3 — more photos means better accuracy.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">2</span><span class="step-title">Tap "Scan &amp; auto-fill"</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">The app sends the photos to Claude AI, which reads the tags and fills in the form fields automatically — country of origin, fabric content, price, currency, garment type, and more.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">3</span><span class="step-title">Review, name, and save</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Enter a <strong>style name</strong> (e.g. "Malibu Pant"). Review the auto-filled fields, make any corrections, then tap <strong>Add sample</strong>.</div>
</div>

<div class="tip-box"><strong>Tip:</strong> The scanner works best with clear, well-lit photos. Hold the phone steady and make sure text on the labels is legible.</div>

<h3>Option B — Enter manually</h3>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">1</span><span class="step-title">Fill in the form</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Enter the style name, select the country, garment type, fabric content, gender, woven/knit, unit cost, and currency using the dropdown menus. You can also add photos (optional) using the photo slots at the top of the form.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">2</span><span class="step-title">Tap "Add sample"</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">The sample is saved to your list. The app remembers the last country and currency you used, so consecutive entries are faster.</div>
</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>Managing your sample list</h2>

<p>Each sample appears as a card showing the style name, garment type, quantity, fabric content, and cost. You'll also see tags for:</p>

<p>
  <span class="tag tag-blue">Italy</span> Country &nbsp;
  <span class="tag tag-green">Photos</span> Has images attached &nbsp;
  <span class="tag tag-purple">Scanned</span> Was auto-filled from photos
</p>

<p>If photos are attached, small thumbnails appear on the card.</p>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">&bull;</span><span class="step-title">Edit a sample</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Tap the <strong>Edit</strong> button on any card to update its details.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">&bull;</span><span class="step-title">Delete a sample</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Tap <strong>Delete</strong> on any card. You'll be asked to confirm before it's removed.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">&bull;</span><span class="step-title">Import from Excel</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Tap <strong>"Import existing .xlsx to continue editing"</strong> at the top to load samples from a previous export file.</div>
</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>Exporting your data</h2>

<p>When you're ready to submit your customs declaration, tap <span class="kbd">&darr; Save</span> at the bottom of the screen. The app produces two files:</p>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">1</span><span class="step-title">Excel file (.xlsx)</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">
    <strong>Tab 1 — Shipment Details:</strong> Your customs declaration data with style names, all fields formatted and styled. Unit costs and totals display the correct currency symbol. Totals are grouped by currency at the bottom.<br><br>
    <strong>Tab 2 — Sample Photos:</strong> Thumbnail images of the price tag, content label, and garment for each sample, embedded directly in the spreadsheet.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">2</span><span class="step-title">ZIP file — full-resolution garment photos</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">A separate ZIP download containing the original high-resolution garment photos, named by style (e.g. <span class="kbd">Malibu_Pant.jpg</span>). These are full camera quality, suitable for 3D rendering or product photography.</div>
</div>

<div class="tip-box"><strong>On mobile:</strong> If you see a <span class="kbd">&uarr; Share</span> button, tap it to send both files via email, AirDrop, WhatsApp, or any sharing method — with the files already attached.</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>After exporting</h2>

<p>Your sample list stays in the app after exporting so you can re-export if needed. When you come back to the app 5 or more minutes after an export, it will ask if you want to clear the list and start fresh for your next session.</p>

<div class="warn-box"><strong>Important:</strong> Photos are stored in your browser's memory during the session. If you have a large number of samples (50+), export at the end of each day to make sure nothing is lost.</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>Settings</h2>

<p>Tap the <span class="kbd">&#9881;</span> gear icon in the top bar to access:</p>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">&bull;</span><span class="step-title">Send-to email address</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Pre-fills the recipient when using the Share feature on mobile. Optional.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">&bull;</span><span class="step-title">Anthropic API key</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Required for the photo scan feature. Your API key will be provided by management. The key is stored on your device only and is never sent anywhere except directly to the Anthropic API.</div>
</div>

<div class="info-box"><strong>Privacy:</strong> All sample data and photos are stored locally on your device. Nothing is uploaded to any server. The only external connection is when you use the photo scan feature, which sends images to the Anthropic API for analysis.</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">?</span><span class="step-title">Photo scan not working</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">Make sure your API key is saved (check the gear icon). You need an internet connection for scanning. If you see an error, the red box will show exactly what went wrong — common issues are invalid API key or no network.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">?</span><span class="step-title">Share button not showing</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">The Share button only appears on mobile devices (iPhone, iPad, Android). On desktop, use the Save button to download files directly.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">?</span><span class="step-title">Data disappeared after reopening</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">If you cleared your browser data or are using private/incognito mode, locally stored data will be lost. Always export before clearing your browser. Photos from large sessions may also exceed browser storage limits — export regularly.</div>
</div>

<div class="step-card">
  <div class="step-header"><span class="step-num">?</span><span class="step-title">Excel not opening correctly</span></div>
  <div class="step-body">The exported file works best in Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets. Some lightweight spreadsheet apps may not display embedded photos in Tab 2.</div>
</div>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<p style="text-align:center;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;margin-top:24px">RD Style Sample Log — Built for the road.</p>

</div>
